LOINC® (Logical Observation Identifiers Names and Codes)
--------------------------------------------------------

This material contains content from LOINC (http://loinc.org). LOINC is
copyright © Regenstrief Institute, Inc. and the Logical Observation
Identifiers Names and Codes (LOINC) Committee and is available at no cost
under the license at http://loinc.org/license. LOINC® is a registered
United States trademark of Regenstrief Institute, Inc.

LOINC content appears in:
  - bundled_config/knowledge/lab_tests.json
  - config/seeds/lab_tests.json

The set of LOINC codes shipped is selected from Wikidata's P4338 mapping
(CC0) and the project's hand-curated seed set — roughly 480 commonly-
referenced laboratory tests. The English display strings on those entries
are taken verbatim from the official LOINC Table's LONG_COMMON_NAME field
(LOINC release 2.82), and SHORTNAME values are added as aliases. Italian,
French, German, and Spanish display strings are taken from the
corresponding official LOINC Linguistic Variants files (Group 3 artifacts
itIT16, frFR18, deDE15, esES12). All such display strings are reproduced
unmodified in accordance with Section 10 of the LOINC license.

Asclepius does not redistribute the full LOINC table; only the display
fields associated with the ~480 codes shipped above. To regenerate or
extend the bundled file, register at https://loinc.org, place
LoincTableCore.csv at scripts/build_knowledge/loinc.csv (and any
LinguisticVariant CSVs at loinc_{it,fr,de,es}.csv), then run
scripts/build_knowledge/build_lab_tests.py.

